  "texts": [
    "The total number of physical qubits required for this encoding is 288.",
    "The distance-18 code from Table 1 would require 576 physical qubits whereas suppressing the error rate from 10 -3 to 2 ×10 -12 enabling nearly hundred billion syndrome cycles.",
    "For comparison, encoding 12 logical qubits into separate patches of the surface code would require more than 3,000 physical qubits to suppress the error rate from 10 -3 to 10 -7 (Fig. 3).",
    "In this example, the distance-12 BB code offers 10 times saving in the number of physical qubits compared with the surface code.A proposal for quantum error correction is only useful if the logical qubits are accessible.",
    "Fortunately, BB LDPC codes possess the required features to act as a logical memory."
